  title: Kill Yr. Idols
  author: Sonic Youth
  album: Kill Yr. Idols
  year: 1983
  description: Sonic Youth was an American rock band formed in New York City in 1981.
    Founding members Kim Gordon (bass, vocals, guitar), Thurston Moore (lead guitar,
    vocals) and Lee Ranaldo (rhythm guitar, vocals) remained together for the entire
    history of the band, while Steve Shelley (drums) followed a series of short-term
    drummers in 1985, rounding out the core line-up. Jim O'Rourke (bass, guitar,
    keyboards) was also a member of the band from 1999 to 2005, and Mark Ibold (bass,
    guitar) was a member from 2006 to 2011.
